<subSubSection id="0F8CB2444565662940EB1E446DE68B95" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CF71CEBA6EF8294AAD7431CE6AB7E67E" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" type="mainText">
<pageBreakToken id="F2E5BF8C012A0A52D7B78A54B6FA5545" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" start="start">Variation</pageBreakToken>
. In Europe and North America the 
<taxonomicName id="F463DAC082AD7A115A0C49DE443CC2A8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hybridum">C. hybridum</taxonomicName>
aggregate comprises two well-delimited taxa, viz. 
<taxonomicName id="74E00CB99FAE172F0764882A4C2CC4F2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hybridum">C. hybridum</taxonomicName>
in Europe and 
<taxonomicName id="DE27EA9EEE1251505638606CC02D5C6C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" genus.bestMatchDistance="44388" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simplex">C. simplex</taxonomicName>
(see rare casuals) in North America. In Asia it is represented by several taxa. A specimen from S Upl Sollentuna (Rotebro) 1925 belongs to one of these, having large leaf-blades and large seeds with coarsely rugulose but not pitted seed-coat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="68E696F38AAB5EDBC86E219D32FD4DF9" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="24079B3771EFCB7AB6FCD72F965066F2" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" type="mainText">
Similar taxa. 
<taxonomicName id="F23073D2C6A220680085CECFB73C0C26" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hybridum">Chenopodium hybridum</taxonomicName>
is vegetatively 
<normalizedToken id="2C03C70996114FE36B57C55A5BE0D080" originalValue="±" pageId="14" pageNumber="18">+/-</normalizedToken>
indistinguishable from the North American 
<taxonomicName id="9B18312691FFF84C43E5DEFEE13D3EB7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" genus.bestMatchDistance="44190" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simplex">C. simplex</taxonomicName>
(rare casual), but clearly different in seed characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
